---
import LegalPage from "../components/LegalPage.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../lib/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use - Aizen"
  description="Terms of Use for Aizen, a macOS developer tool by Vivy Technologies Co., Limited."
  canonicalPath="/terms"
  ogType="article"
>
  <LegalPage title="Terms of Use" lastUpdated="April 10, 2026">
    <section>
      <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By downloading, installing, or using Aizen ("the App"), you agree to these Terms of Use. If
        you do not agree, do not use the App.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Product Scope</h2>
      <p>
        Aizen is a macOS application for managing Git worktrees with integrated terminal, file
        browser, web browser, and AI agent support via the Agent Client Protocol (ACP). The currently
        supported platform is macOS with Apple Silicon.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Licensing</h2>
      <p>
        Source code published at <a href={SITE.githubUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{SITE.githubUrl}</a>
        {" "}is licensed under GPL-3.0.
      </p>
      <h3>Free Version</h3>
      <p>The free version of Aizen may be used without charge, subject to any feature limitations.</p>
      <h3>Aizen Pro</h3>
      <p>
        Aizen Pro requires a valid license. Each license is valid for a single user and may be
        activated on multiple devices owned by that user.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Restrictions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You may not use the App for unlawful purposes.</li>
        <li>You may not remove or alter any proprietary notices in official binaries.</li>
        <li>You may not share, distribute, or sublicense your license key.</li>
        <li>You may not misrepresent modified builds as official Aizen releases.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        Aizen integrates with third-party AI agents (Claude, Codex, Gemini, etc.). Your use of these
        services is subject to their respective terms of service. We are not responsible for the
        content or responses generated by these AI services.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. Pricing</h2>
      <p>
        The current pricing is a free core app, a Pro subscription ($5.99/mo or $59/yr), and a
        one-time Lifetime purchase ($179). Billing is handled by Stripe. We offer a 30-day
        money-back guarantee.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        THE APP IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. WE DO NOT WARRANT
        THAT THE APP WILL BE UNINTERRUPTED, ERROR-FREE, OR SUITABLE FOR EVERY WORKFLOW.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        IN NO EVENT SHALL VIVY TECHNOLOGIES CO., LIMITED BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL,
        SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES ARISING OUT OF YOUR USE OF THE APP OR WEBSITE.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>9. Termination</h2>
      <p>
        We may terminate your license if you violate these terms. Upon termination, you must cease
        all use of the App and destroy all copies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>10. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms shall be governed by the laws of Hong Kong SAR, without regard to its conflict of
        law provisions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about these Terms, contact <a href="mailto:dev@aizen.win">dev@aizen.win</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </LegalPage>
</BaseLayout>
